Although the limits which he assigns are so wide as to comprehend a vast number of examples‚ and practically it will be found very difficult, if not impossible, to fix upon any limits at all, yet we shall have no difficulty in enumerating the different cases in which the licence‚ if we can call it so, is most common, and in which there is no reasonable ground for altering the text on this account alone.
